:Def4: (for A being (Subset of X) holds (A in ( sigma_Field C ) implies ( it . A ) = ( C . A )));
existence
proof
(ex D being (Function of ( sigma_Field C ),( ExtREAL )) st (for A being (Subset of X) holds (A in ( sigma_Field C ) implies ( D . A ) = ( C . A ))))
proof
deffunc F(set) = ( C . $1 );
A1: (for S being set holds (S in ( sigma_Field C ) implies F(S) in ( ExtREAL )));
consider D being (Function of ( sigma_Field C ),( ExtREAL )) such that A2: (for S being set holds (S in ( sigma_Field C ) implies ( D . S ) = F(S))) from FUNCT_2:sch 2(A1);
